<Content_wSideColumn ID="x64480" Name="Pathway Pass-along Cards" Layout="byuidefault.xsl"><Title type="string" label="Title" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Pathway Pass-along Cards</Title><Abstract type="string" label="Abstract" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Information on how to use Pass-along cards</Abstract><xPower Type="GroupStart" GroupStart="" Name="SideColumn" label="L/R Column" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" Expanded="false"><MoveLeft type="boolean" label="Toggle column right or left (right is default)" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false">false</MoveLeft><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="ImageComponent" label="Image Component" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="LeftColumnImageComponent" Expanded="false"/><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="TextComponent" label="Text Component" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="ColumnTextComponent" Expanded="false"/><fbookTop type="boolean" label="Put facebook at top of page" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false">false</fbookTop><fbookStatus type="string" label="Facebook ID#" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"></fbookStatus><fbookToken type="string" label="Access_Token" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"></fbookToken><fbookDisplayed type="string" label="Number of facebook messages to display" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false">1</fbookDisplayed></xPower><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Body Copy" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<p><br />Pass-along cards can be an effective way of generating interest in the program.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img alt="Pass along cards" height="302" src="Images/Admin_Offices/Online%20Learning/icons/passalonglabel1.jpg" style="vertical-align: middle;" width="403" /></p>
<p>Pass-along cards are designed to quickly display a small amount of information about the program, targeting a wide audience. Effective ways to use pass-along cards include:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong><strong><strong>Download</strong><span style="font-weight: normal;">&nbsp;</span><span style="font-weight: normal;"><a href="Documents/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Online Instruction/5195newrevised.doc">AVERY 5195(return address label)</a></span><span style="font-weight: normal;">&nbsp;or other compatible label template, add your contact information and place in designated place on brochures.</span></strong></strong>
<ul style="font-weight: normal;">
<li>To copy information into all labels quickly write up contact information into first cell, select cell and copy, next bring the cursor above each column of labels and click to select the entire row; paste copied information, this should copy the information into each label cell of the entire row. &nbsp;Repeat for remaining rows.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Use them like a business card.&nbsp;</strong>Pass-along cards are designed for portability and accessibility. &nbsp;Take every opportunity to hand them out.</li>
<li><strong>Give them to local leaders &amp; Institutes</strong>: Take a stack to your local Institute and ask them to set them out. Give them to local priesthood leaders. This will keep the program in the front of their mind and makes it easier for them to refer students. Give them to LDS Services and Employment where possible.</li>
<li><strong>Give them to students:</strong> Make sure your current students have plenty to give out to their family and friends.</li>
</ul>
<h3>How to get them</h3>
<p>You can request pass-along cards by filling out the&nbsp;<a href="https://cms.byui.edu/home/AcademicTechnology/OnlineLearning/Path/_layouts/listform.aspx?PageType=8&amp;ListId={2F3B27DA-B570-4B33-A8FD-2767B55F97EF}&amp;RootFolder=">Missionary Marketing Order Form</a>.&nbsp;You can also download a pdf version below. Note: These files may take a moment to download.</p>
